title.narrative: DGC- Aga Khan Foundation GDA - Yetu Initiative

description.narrative: (Kenya): .Yetu initiative will build on the achievements of the first two phases, to support Local Development Organizations (LDOs) in Kenya through the Kaunti Kuimarisha Uendelevu - Strengthening County Sustainability - Annual Program Statement (APS). Yetu will engage country-wide LDOs to foster community-led, community-managed, and community-owned development, a main principle of J2SR. Yetu will also build LDOs' capacity in community philanthropy to leverage assets, abilities, and trust in addressing local development. This will catalyze the sustainability of local civil society..Yetu will support successful APS applicants to engage county stakeholders in the co-creation and formation of LDOs. Once registered, Yetu will support the LDOs to design strategic plans that incorporate county priorities, context and systems findings. The initiative will support LDO members through a blend of courses, networking opportunities, and in-person mentorship. Consequently, this will strengthen the community of practice. Through Yetu's support, LDOs will work with county authorities to influence local development priorities based on members' and citizen's needs. The activity will also support LDOs to lead in priority setting, outreach to vulnerable and marginalized populations, and partner with county governments and the private sector to coordinate COVID-19 responses. It will also mobilize local resources to address the pandemic and its secondary effects. The Interventions will engage county governments, private sector, and civil society to support LDOs to be resilient and citizen-responsive to drive inclusive growth, all critical to Kenya's journey to self-reliance. Importantly, Yetu initiative supports Kenya's Joint Strategic Plan by ensuring stability and building citizen-responsive local governance that will help transform lives, communities, and economies in Kenya.
